      1          /**
      2           *  @file
      3           *  @brief      Proportional-Integral Controller
      4           *
      5           *  @details    A PI-Lead controller is a proportional gain in parallel with an integrator;
      6           *              both in series with a lead controller. The proportional gain provides fast error response.
      7           *              The integrator drives the system to a 0 steady-state error.
      8           *              See Pe13-1_Odra_Mci.doc for theoretical basis and how to derive A, B, C coefficients.
      9           *
     10           *  @Module_Owner{Lucien Lee from Delta}
     11           *  $Revision: 1.2 $
     12           *
     13           *  Copyright 2011 Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     14           */
